	<body>
		<segment id="1" parent="9" relname="list">I thank you, Madam President, for this opportunity to speak before the Security Council.</segment>
		<segment id="2" parent="8" relname="conjunction">I thank Council members for understanding the critical situation in Ukraine</segment>
		<segment id="3" parent="8" relname="conjunction">and for their support.</segment>
		<segment id="4" parent="5" relname="preparation">Before getting into the substance of my statement this evening,</segment>
		<segment id="5" parent="12" relname="span">I would like start by mentioning that today Christians worldwide celebrate a great holiday, the day of the entry of our Lord into Jerusalem, Palm Sunday.</segment>
		<segment id="6" parent="11" relname="span">Unfortunately, today the celebration is falling under the shadow of aggression and bloodshed in Ukraine.</segment>
		<segment id="7" parent="11" relname="elaboration">On the eve of the holiday, terrorists coordinated by agents of the Russian Federation seized control of State buildings in several cities of the Donetsk region.</segment>
